cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CR

This paper discusses the architecture and performance modeling of a system for peering arrangements between Content Delivery Networks (CDNs) to improve overall service and reduce costs. The paper focuses on network infrastructure and performance, which suggests that the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses policy management and Quality of Service (QoS), which could place it in the categories of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of modeling and prediction techniques could also place it in the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
